      "role": "user",
      "content": "right but isn't that kind of a circular argument? like, you're basically saying that the way certain groups talk is a marker of their lack of opportunity. and since AAVE is so closely tied to black communities, aren't you essentially saying that black speakers are inherently less \"academically capable\" or \"sophisticated\" because of their dialect? it feels like you're just reinforcing the idea that white, middle-class ways of speaking are the only real standard for being smart.",
